quran[31]{c,v,t}:
  76,1,"Doth not a long time pass over MAN, during which he is a thing unremembered"
  76,2,"We have created man from the union of the sexes that we might prove him; and hearing, seeing, have we made him"
  76,3,"In a right way have we guided him, be he thankful or ungrateful"
  76,4,For the Infidels we have got ready chains and collars and flaming fire
  76,5,But a wine cup tempered at the camphor fountain the just shall quaff
  76,6,"Fount whence the servants of God shall drink, and guide by channels from place to place"
  76,7,"They who fulfilled their vows, and feared the day whose woes will spread far and wide"
  76,8,"Who though longing for it themselves, bestowed their food on the poor and the orphan and the captive"
  76,9,"We feed you for the sake of God: we seek from you neither recompense nor thanks"
  76,10,A stern and calamitous day dread we from our Lord
  76,11,From the evil therefore of that day hath God delivered them and cast on them brightness of face and joy
  76,12,"And hath rewarded their constancy, with Paradise and silken robes"
  76,13,"Reclining therein on bridal couches, nought shall they know of sun or piercing cold"
  76,14,"Its shades shall be close over them, and low shall its fruits hang down"
  76,15,And vessels of silver and goblets like flagons shall be borne round among them
  76,16,Flagons of silver whose measure themselves shall mete
  76,17,And there shall they be given to drink of the cup tempered with zendjebil (ginger)
  76,18,From the fount therein whose name is Selsebil (the softly flowing)
  76,19,Aye-blooming youths go round among them. When thou lookest at them thou wouldest deem them scattered pearls
  76,20,"And when thou seest this, thou wilt see delights and a vast kingdom"
  76,21,"Their clothing green silk robes and rich brocade: with silver bracelets shall they be adorned; and drink of a pure beverage shall their Lord give them"
  76,22,This shall be your recompense. Your efforts shall meet with thanks
  76,23,We ourselves have sent down to thee the Koran as a missive from on high
  76,24,"Await then with patience the judgments of thy Lord, and obey not the wicked among them and the unbelieving"
  76,25,"And make mention of the name of thy Lord at morn, at even"
  76,26,"And at night. Adore him, and praise him the livelong night"
  76,27,"But these men love the fleeting present, and leave behind them the heavy day of doom"
  76,28,"Ourselves have we created them, and strengthened their joints; and when we please, with others like unto themselves will we replace them"
  76,29,"This truly is a warning: And whoso willeth, taketh the way to his Lord"
  76,30,"But will it ye shall not, unless God will it, for God is Knowing, Wise"
  76,31,"He causeth whom He will to enter into his mercy. But for the evil doers, He hath made ready an afflictive chastisement"